main event: Personnel at Chitose Air Base observed three unidentified flying objects in the sky on September 6, 1957.
interesting points: The objects were seen through breaks in the cloud cover and appeared to be hovering or moving slowly,The sighting lasted for approximately 10 minutes,Multiple photographs of similar circular objects with wing or tail structures are included in the report,The sightings occurred during a U.S. Air Force investigation related to Project Blue Book,There were four specific black and white photographs linked to the sighting.
witness description: personnel of the Base Weather Station
